OL,3,CDevon councillor expelled from Reform
OL,4,Cwas 'ostracised' by party, he says
OL,6,FIn a statement, Reform UK said Mr
OL,7,FHill's actions "damaged the interests
OL,8,Fof the party". The letter in question
OL,9,Fwas calling for national auto-
OL,10,Fenrolment of free meals, which Mr Hill
OL,11,Fargues would "transform the lives of
OL,12,Fthousands of children across Devon and
OL,13,Fthe UK".
OL,15,FCllr Michael Fife Cook, Leader of the
OL,16,FReform Group on Devon Council, said:
OL,17,F"Irrespective of something being a
OL,18,Fgood cause, attaching councillors'
OL,19,Fnames to a letter without their
OL,20,Fconsent is totally unacceptable
OL,21,Fbehaviour.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/10
