OL,4,Cwas 'ostracised' by party, he says
OL,6,F"In the absence of any objections or
OL,7,Fdirect communication to the contrary,
OL,8,FI reasonably and in good faith
OL,9,Finterpreted this as consent," Mr Hill
OL,10,Fsaid in a statement.
OL,12,F"Let's be clear: this incident is
OL,13,Fbeing used as a pretext," he added.
